{{Quote|They say I'm the worst kind of pirate, ambushing unarmed ships to steal their cargoes. I say that's the best kind of pirate.|[[Kath Scarlet]]|<ref name="SWGTCG">{{SWGTCG|set=Squadrons Over Corellia|cardname=Kath Scarlet}}</ref>}}
The '''Binayre Pirates''' were a band of [[Pirate/Legends|pirates]] and [[Smuggler/Legends|smugglers]] that operated within the [[Corellian sector/Legends|Corellian sector]] during the [[Galactic Civil War/Legends|Galactic Civil War]].

==Description==
{{Quote|Have you seen those guys!? They'd kill us! Uhh, I mean, they'd kill us if we - if we showed up without weapons!|A commoner, to a spacer|<ref name="SWG:Ac">{{SWGcite|exp=AED|type=herald|A commoner|Talus}}</ref>}}
[[File:BinayrePirate-SWZ.png|thumb|left|250px|The pirates made use of Z-95-AF4 Headhunters.]]
The Binayre Pirates operated in the Corellian sector<ref name="CDAG" /> and were led by [[Captain/Legends|Captain]] [[Kath Scarlet]].<ref name="SoC-DS" /> The Binayre maintained two home bases on the twin worlds [[Talus/Legends|Talus]] and [[Tralus/Legends|Tralus]], and were among the lowest criminal elements on those worlds.<ref name="CDAG" /> They were looked down upon as disreputable and untrustworthy even by other criminals.<ref name="BS">{{SWGTCG|set=Champions of the Force (SWGTCG)|cardname=Binayre Swindler}}</ref> Several of them wore the insignia of [[Black Sun/Legends|Black Sun]].<ref name="SoC-DS" /> On Talus, they operated from their [[Binayre Pirate Bunker|bunker]].<ref name="SWG:BPB" /> The Binayre Pirates were tracked by the [[Corellian Security Force]] and the [[Federation of the Double Worlds]], and they were also in open conflict with the [[Aa'kuan]] anarchist.<ref name="FS">{{SonyCite|url=content.jsp?page=Faction%20Standings|text=Faction Standings}}</ref> After the [[Battle of Yavin/Legends|Battle of Yavin]], the Binayre Pirates controlled several areas of space in the [[Corellian system/Legends|Corellian system]], including the [[Binayre Razorcat]],<ref name="SCCS">{{SonyCite|url=en_US/players/content.vm?id=66847&resource=features|text=Star Chart: Corellia System}}</ref> the [[Trifecta Star]] and the [[Rayless Lantern]].<ref name="BP">{{SWGTCG|set=Champions of the Force (SWGTCG)|cardname=Binayre Pirate}}</ref> In space battles, the pirates flew [[M3-A Scyk interceptor/Legends|M3-A Scyk fighters]]<ref name="SWG:JtL">''[[Star Wars Galaxies: Jump to Lightspeed]]''</ref> or [[Z-95-AF4 Headhunter/Legends|Z-95-AF4 Headhunters]].<ref name="FFGXW2">{{FFGXW2|set=Scum and Villainy Conversion Kit|cardname=Binayre Pirate}}</ref>

==History==
{{Quote|Those Binyare will think twice before crossing the Empire again.|[[Ceth Laike]], to an Imperial operative|<ref name="SWG:E">{{SWGcite|exp=JtL|type=faction|Imperial|Enough!!|Talus}}</ref>}}
[[File:Binayre_Swindler.jpg|thumb|right|200px|A Binayre swindler.]]
In [[1 ABY/Legends|1 ABY]],<ref name="SWG_timeline">{{SWG_timeline}}</ref> a commoner in the city of [[Dearic/Legends|Dearic]] provided the coordinates of the Binayre Pirate Bunker on Talus to a [[Spacer/Legends|spacer]] brave enough to visit it.<ref name="SWG:Ac" /> Later, [[Jabba Desilijic Tiure/Legends|Jabba the Hutt's]] [[Bounty hunter/Legends|bounty hunter]] [[Bronell]] dispatched a spacer to the Talusian pirate bunker in order to retrieve information about a [[Corellian Security Force|CorSec]] officer who owned money to Jabba, as well as to the pirates.<ref name="SWG:B">{{SWGcite|exp=AED|type=other|Corellian Corvette Pre-Quest: "Bronell"}}</ref>

The same year, an [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Imperial]] [[TIE/sa tactical bomber/Legends|TIE bomber]] crash-landed on Talus during a [[Battle on Talus|battle]] between the Galactic Empire and the [[Alliance to Restore the Republic/Legends|Rebel Alliance]]. Although the Empire quickly dispatched a rescue ream, the first to find the crash site were a group of Binayre scalawags.<ref name="SWG:E" /> Looking for ship parts to salvage,<ref name="P14.1">{{SonyForumsCite|url=swg/board/message?board.id=swgpatchnotes&message.id=734|text=Update Notes: Publish 14.1 - March 24, 2005}}</ref> the criminals assassinated the Imperial pilot on the spot. The Binayres then attacked the group of Imperial operatives sent to rescue the pilot but they were all killed. The Imperial later reported to [[Imperial officer/Legends|Imperial Officer]] [[Ceth Laike]]. In retaliation, the officer ordered the Imperial operatives to strike at several criminal and [[Pirate/Legends|pirate]] groups in the Corellian system. On Talus, the operatives assaulted a Binayre camp and killed 15 of them. Then, Imperial pilots attacked a group of Binayre starfighters in Corellian space. All pirate vessels were destroyed and the Binayre leader [[MacDougal|"Black Jack" MacDougal]] was killed in the battle.<ref name="SWG:E" /> Troops of the Imperial [[419th Infantry]] were also involved in actions against Binayre Pirates.<ref name="419th">{{SWGTCG|set=The Shadow Syndicate|cardname=419th Infantry Major}}</ref>

Around the same time, Kath Scarlet and a group of Binayres pirates struggled on Talus against a spacer and an [[Imperial Security Bureau/Legends|Imperial Security Bureau]] team led by [[Jeffren Brek]] for the control of the [[Z-95 Headhunter/Legends|Z-95 Headhunter]] ''[[Dire Hound]]''.<ref name="SoC-LS">{{SWGTCG|set=Squadrons Over Corellia|scenario=Light Side scenario campaign}}</ref>

